SCIENTIFIC-ATLANTA LICENSES INTERACTIVE TRANSACTION

Scientific-Atlanta has licensed interactive transaction encryption
technology and algorithms for the PowerKey conditional access system it
is developing for its line of digital cable TV equipment.  RSA Data
Security's public key encryption engine circuitry will be embedded in a
microprocessor to provide security for interactive video applications.
Scientific-Atlanta has also licensed the patents from Cylink Corp.
which cover the public key encryption practices implemented by RSA's
algorithms.

