TEXAS INSTRUMENTS DEMONSTRATES TV SYSTEM

Texas Instruments has demonstrated what it claims is the industry's
first end-to-end, digital progressive-scanning TV system, as part of a
recent Federal Communications Commission hearing on advanced TV.
Others demonstrating digital TV systems were CBS Inc., Hitachi America
Ltd., Hubbard Broadcasting Inc., Microsoft Corp., NBC, Sony Corp.  of
America and the HDTV Grand Alliance.  TI's demonstration included the
company's Digital Micromirror Device (DMD) microchip-based 50-inch rear-
projection system.  The digital source material shown on TI's digital
projection system was encoded by a 525-line progressive-scanning real-
time MPEG-2 encoder that TI custom-developed for NTV, Japan's leading
private TV network.

